caption: Alice is definitely one of my favorite spots in Dallas to go out on a date night or girls night out. Their food is amazing, the service is great and the place is very chick and beautiful. I never get tired of coming back. 100% recommend.
Small and very intimate location. Their selection of Japanese whiskey was amazing but was not over shadowed by the amazing food. Will definitely becoming back.
Great service,  sushi,  and drinks!

The intimate atmosphere and cocktails were incredible— the bar staff is super talented and will craft you a 5-star cocktail. The food was very mediocre. We tried the brussels (always good!), rainbow roll, pad Thai and duck fried rice. The …
Great service and the brussels sprouts were so good!
I get to eat here a lot since I work nearby. I like how their customer service is always good and they keep the place neat at all times. Pricing is affordable and they serve large portions.

I walked in & felt as if this was my home bar. Ricky is an incredible bartender!! He took great care of myself & my friend. She tried an espresso martini, which would normally make me cringe... but it was really good. The man knows his stuff!!
Girls out number guys but dress nice tour looking at 12$+ a drink

The food and drinks were both great. The service was great. And their COVID protocols were even better. They were taking temperatures at the door, had hand sanitizer at all the tables, and our glasses and silverware came wrapped in plastic. It was a great experience and we'll definitely be back!
Great spot for food, nice staff and good meeting spot for friends
Awesome place!
Delicious tapas and creative cocktails. Expect a cool Miami 80s chic vibe and decor with plenty of 80s jams playing. Don’t miss the Kimchi Lo Main or Yellowtail Sashimi!
The atmosphere was great.  The cocktails were tasty.  The food is just meh.  I was really hoping for the food to be out of this world delicious but it wasn't.

Everything we tried was excellent, dumplings, steamed buns, ribs, sushi, and a couple other dishes.  All dishes were well portioned for sharing among four to five people.  Most could also be a small entrée for one. Service was not super attentive on things like drink refills, but they were lightly staffed as everyone seems to be now.

Had the best birthday here. The staff is extremely nice and welcoming, the DJ was very fun. The food was delicious- the espresso martinis were the best.  Will definitely be returning, thank you Alice!
I can't remember the last time I ate so much in my life! The food is just that damn good! The Brussels, Crab Claws, & Beef Tenderloins had me spinning🤤🤤🤤
I love visiting here. The staff was very welcoming and sociable. Prices were average for the menu. Reminds me of a place in New York I loved to visit.
The staff was sociable and attentive.
Great food and cocktails. Ricky is the best!!! Amazing service. Definitely check this spot out!
It was so fresh. Service is consistently above par. This place has a nice atmosphere. Feels similar to a cafe in Chicago I liked.
One of the best spots in the area. I've had nothing but enjoyable experiences here and plan to keep visiting.

Went here for my bachelorette party-reserved a spot for my party and felt rushed out, though we were buying drinks and food consistently, because they ‘had another reservation’ they had booked. Not sure why you’d book reservations that …
Arrived at six, it was not packed. Certainly worth a return visit. The place has an awesome feel to it.

For the price Alice is a decent pick for a night out on the town. The food was good, nothing out of the ordinary but nothing bad. The best dish I had was the tenderloin, the flavor was quite unique. My least favorite was the chicken soba, …

Update: came back a second time and the food was just as good. Solid recommendation.  Im not sure if the were just having an "ON" night, but the flavors are SO GOOD! The duck potstickers, ahi tower, sushi, and tenderloin are all very good. …
Cute little chill vibes atmosphere, and they play great music.
i will be back with my relatives. prices that are reasonable. i see why this place has a lot of positive reviews.
great spot for an appetite of any size. service is typically above par. bring your appetite because portions are generous.
Nice place.
Cute restaurant! Small and cozy. The crab claws are amazing. Love their sushi 👍🏼 Photo op right outside of the front door. Parking is a little difficult, but worth it!
entered near eleven, it wasn't packed. i will be back with my coworkers.
It's so tasty. The staff was very welcoming and sociable. The bill was good for how much you get.
The FOOD here is incredible! Definitely worth the price. My husband and I had Duck fried rice, pork ribs, calamari. Their drinks are strong and smooth. Will come back again!!
Possibly the best spot to eat, drink, and make memories on Ross Ave.
It was so savory. I had a cousin come into town and she asked me to go back here. It has a cool feel to it.
Prices were good for how much you get.
service is always excellent even when they have a full house. looking forward to returning with my coworkers. it has a nice atmosphere. if it wasn't far from my work i would come by more.

Only positive thing was the atmosphere. The food was honestly terrible. The chicken egg rolls tasted like fish and the pad thai was mushy and way too spicy. However, the biggest turn off for me was the owner. He was very rude. I will not be going back for a long time

Very rude staff. From the time I walked in. The “owner” yelled at my friend for being late for her reservation. He also snatched me by my arm to tell me he needed to take my temperature. And the waitress was very rude. She acted as if she …
Great service and delicious food.  Good music too.
Came for a friends birthday dinner tonight and the food was so good. Our server was very tentative to our table and provided great service. Always one of my favorite spots!
Great atmosphere, food was delish and Maria (our server) provided exceptional service. Sanitization efforts were next level here too.  Definitely one of our best dining experiences in Dallas.

Delicious food! My husband and I really enjoyed eating dinner here at the end of our honeymoon. I appreciated that they took each guests temperature, wore masks, and took every safety precaution. The food was great. I don’t like sushi, but …
Food was excellent and creative and service was awesome
Excellent first time experience. Covid practices in place. Service was great!
Classy, great service, reasonably priced and a great menu. I loved everything about this place.
The atmosphere was fun; a funky- chic,  Florida deco,  tiki,  lounge, but the food offerings weren't anything as exciting or delicious.

We came here at about 8:45 on a Thursday night and just a heads-up; the music is cool and 80's and loud so if you want a quiet experience come earlier. Starting out Super-NIce bartender that was kind to notice my underaged daughter and …
The shu mai dumplings are very good.
Tried a large variety of dishes, all were excellent!
Fantastic meal, and great variety of cuisines. Very old-classic elegant feel, with a lot of throwback references that brought comfort the moment we walked through the door.
Delicious! Great staff!

What a great place and atmosphere this place has!  We were invited with friends to meet for dinner here.  I never knew the menu and I was very happy to find that they had sushi.  I could eat sushi anytime of the day.
Great food and excellent staff, sat at the bar,  Zack very personable and helpful.

We reserved the private room for my 30th birthday, and I want to rave about Alice! For starters, it’s tough to find a space downtown that will happily accommodate 25 guests. I tried. The folks at Alice we’re friendly and accommodating in …
honestly my favorite evening place. definitely worth a return visit. this place has a great design. ambience is similar to fresno's scene.

Alice is without a doubt one of the best restaurants in Dallas. They perfectly fuse Asian cuisines to create interesting and flawlessly executed dishes. You must try the Steamed Bun but ask for the off-menu option as it will blow your away. …
Great place for cocktails and small bites. José and the other bartenders are top notch. I highly recommend Alice!
Certainly a top place in the area. I'll return with my friends. Reminds me of a place in New York I liked to visit.

This place was phenomenal. We had a group of about 10 and were seated quickly with a reservation we made earlier that day. The place is VERY small so we were thrilled to have a table. We must have tried 15 different dishes. It was …
Solid place for a drink and good music
Do not leave if it's busy, it is worth it.
Food was super flavorful. The staff was very helpful and welcoming. Prices were fair for the quality of the food.
From the 80's Alice in Wonderland vibes to the well decorated and the amazing food this place is a must visit restaurant in Dallas. The chefs are very skilled and the drinks are superb 10/10!

Super chill place!! Food is a little pricey for the portion size but more than makes up for it in taste. Music and environment are super nice. Reservations are a thing so be sure to plan for that if you go!! 1000/10 would recommend and return.
I work here.
Small/unique restaurant with good food. I recommend the dumplings and mandarin vanilla cheesecake.
Cute place love the theme, Aline in wonderland is one of my faves. Drinks are good and the sushi is fresh 👌 love it.
Cool ambiance, food was underwhelming

The food was amazing! Went on a Wednesday night for the DJ and Sushi and Cocktail Specials and it was worth it. Sat in the back dining area and it was the perfect noise level and the ambiance was spot on. Will be returning on future date nights.

Attended a group event at Alice. Valet pay is only $5 and highly recommend. The DJ mixed great tunes. I would only recommend going to have a drink there not to eat. We had to wait 30 minutes for our table. On Wednesday it's Happy Hour all …

Hidden gem. Well curated menu, great cocktails & divine customer service from the valet to the concierge & all the way to the bartender when you sit down & get served. & DJ Blake Ward is the reason I discovered this place & creates the perfect ambiance with his lounge music set.

Food was amazing!  I don’t like shrimp but I ended up eating three of the shrimp with the green flakes (I forget what the dish is called).  It was packed at 10:30pm on a Friday.  It was loud so it made it hard to hear.  The music was awesome though.

A very cute little comfortable chic getaway located a short distance from downtown. My husband made a reservation which unfortunately we were late for but still granted. Friday evening at 7 pm was FULL! Very few seating for walk-ins and the …
Great food! Their salmon was perfect. And the yellow tail sashimi and Alice roll. Also recommend the shishito peppers.
The bar congested the flow of going in and out. The food was tastey!

Loved it! Its a small restaurant and bar but the atmosphere is high energy. There was a DJ that kept the hits playing. Food was amazing. Mostly shareable small plates. Bar mad great drinks including non-alcoholic drinks. There is a private …
Very nice atmosphere. Great service. Excellent Pan Asian. You are depriving yourself if you don't try the calamari.

Great date spot. There are only about 12 tables so it is pretty intimate and reminded me of Tei Tei Robata. The menu is innovative and so are the cocktails. They have a great old fashioned and don't miss the ribs and spring rolls
Such a fun spot! Great food, atmosphere and service.  Can't wait to go back.

This place has a cool design and sexy menu! The food fits for foodies and the crafted cocktails were amazing! We had the dim sum, beef lettuce wraps and the shrimps. All were delicious and fresh. It was the perfect light meal to start our night out.
Awesome venue just extremely small and a bit too loud for intimate conversations.
Food was good, service was great. Bill was more than it should be for the amount of food. Ordered 12 items for 3 people
Amazing food.  Fabulous fun atmosphere Loved it
Very cute restaurant, the food was better than decent. I'd go again.
Amazing atmosphere. Amazing food. Amazing service. What more can you ask for.

Everything we had was DELICIOUS!!!!!! We did have to wait almost an hour to sit down despite having a reservation, but the staff was extremely apologetic and took care of a few of our appetizers, which made it all worth it. Can’t wait to go back!

Best meal we've had out recently.  Ordered bunch of stuff, everything was super tasty.  Friendly and professional staff - spaced out the dishes perfectly.  Good value relative to overall quality  - good cocktails, reasonably priced wine list with unique options.  Cozy atmosphere, 80's tunes were the mot juste!
Loved the Brussels sprouts and my cocktail.  Friendly and knowledgeable bar tender.

The food is great and the place has a great little vibe.  The Clementine Old Fashion and Alice Mule are worth ordering again.  We had the special hot/cold oysters, Hamachi Crudo, Tuna Tartare, Brisket Steamed Buns, and Egg Noodles.. all …
When I say this is the best meal and customer service I’ve had in Dallas I’m not exaggerating. Make a reservation and GO!
Great vibe, good food and service is great. Unique and small atmosphere, but perfect

Every plate was delicious, packed with surprising flavors.  We had 70% of the available dishes.  Service is top notch; they act as a team.  Decor and setting is thoughtfully designed and seating is comfortable.

Bar was mostly full on a Wednesday night around 10pm. Barkeep was very friendly and made a mocktail and poured a tall saporo beer. The brussel sprouts can be ordered without oyster sauce and were delicious! I recommend Alice as a great start to a night. It is a block away from pilikia a fun lounge and dance venue!
New spot in Dallas. The ambience is fantastic. Food is way above average and the drinks are great. The staff is also very friendly. Highly recommended

Had a really good experience! Favorites: Tuna Tartare & Lettuce Wraps More: We went on Friday night @ 9:30p. Friendly staff with good recommendations. Cozy atmosphere with dim lights. Great for a date night. We had drinks at bar while table was getting ready. Have five items, enjoyed them all.
Dude. This place is legit. Small portions so order several things. Sticky buns a must
Sneaky shellfish ingredients.

We ordered the Yuzu Gimlet, Lychee Martini, Clementine Old Fashioned, and a colada type cocktail. All were good, although the Gimlet was preferred.  Food wise: shishito and edamame, crispy tofu salad, tuna tartare, egg noodles, pork buns, …
Great food, great service, great drinks
